New Records: West Indies won the match by five wickets.
Roston Chase scored 42 runs in an unbeaten innings.
Sese Bao scored 50 runs for Papua New Guinea.
Key Match Events: Andre Russell helped West Indies cross the target with six balls to spare.
The match was part of Group C in the T20 World Cup.
Post-Match Reflections: West Indies captain Rovman Powell mentioned the team was 60% in their performance.
Papua New Guinea captain Assad Vala noted they missed a few runs but were proud of their effort.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was co-hosted by the West Indies.
Papua New Guinea showed resilience and fought well despite early wickets.
